You should see an increase in permanence with TPaw now. I've compressed the site's less frequently updated CSS and Javascript files - but kept their uncompressed counterparts for good measure. 

On the CSS front, I moved all common elements that make up the site's design to a single file. Then I moved the customized part to a separate css file. Basically:
```
/* tpaw.core.css */
#core_logo {
    background-image: url("../../imgs/logo.png");
}
```
```
/* core.css  (uncompressed) */
#core_logo {
    position: absolute;
    float: left;
    z-index: 1;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 8px 0 rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2), 0 6px 20px 0 rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.19);
    height: 139px;
    width: 139px;
}
```
